text:
One from a lucid urn of starry dew
Did bathe his luminous limbs, as if to embalm them;
Another cropped her abundant tresses, and threw
The wreath on him, like unto an anadem,
Which, instead of pearls, with frozen tears did gem;
Another, in her stubborn grief, would break
Her bow and winged reeds, as though to stem
A greater loss with one that was more weak;
And blunt the barbèd fire against his frozen cheek.

source_text:
One from a lucid urn of starry dew
Washed his light limbs as if embalming them;
Another clipped her profuse locks, and threw
The wreath upon him, like an anadem,
Which frozen tears instead of pearls begem;
Another in her wilful grief would break
Her bow and winged reeds, as if to stem
A greater loss with one which was more weak;
And dull the barbed fire against his frozen cheek.
